main event: Residents in Winona, Minnesota observed a red ball with a trail of smoke and burning particles on October 20, 1948.
interesting points: The incident was reported in the Minneapolis Morning Tribune., A similar sighting was reported involving a flying object that broke up into bright particles., Witnesses described the object as being about 25 feet long and 5 feet wide., The object's actions were stated to be puzzling and different from conventional aircraft., No further investigation was conducted by the Air Force regarding this sighting.
sighted object: a red ball with a trail of smoke and burning particles
